## 📌 What Is This File?

`SubmissionService.java` is the **service layer** responsible for every submission-related operation on the SolveStack platform. When a Developer submits a solution to a challenge, that submission passes through this service — it is validated, registered in the platform-wide registry, linked to the Challenge, and tracked by the Developer.

This class sits between the model layer (`Submission`, `Developer`, `Challenge`) and the rest of the application, making sure all business rules are enforced consistently in one place.

