## 🔐 Guard Conditions in `submitSolution()`

`submitSolution()` is the most important method in this class. It runs five checks before creating anything:

| # | Check | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Developer is not null | Prevents NullPointerException |
| 2 | Developer is logged in | Enforces authentication |
| 3 | Challenge is not null | Prevents NullPointerException |
| 4 | Challenge status is OPEN | Prevents late or invalid submissions |
| 5 | Developer hasn't already submitted | Prevents duplicate entries |
| 6 | Solution text passes `validateSubmission()` | Ensures quality content |

Only after all six pass does the submission get created and registered.

---

## 🔄 Submission Status Lifecycle

A submission moves through these states in order:

```
[Created] ──► PENDING ──► UNDER_REVIEW ──► ACCEPTED
                                      └──► REJECTED
              └──► WITHDRAWN  (Developer retracts before review)
```

- `PENDING` → Default state when first submitted
- `UNDER_REVIEW` → Evaluator has picked it up
- `ACCEPTED` → Evaluator approved the solution
- `REJECTED` → Evaluator rejected the solution
- `WITHDRAWN` → Developer pulled it back (only possible from PENDING)

`updateSubmissionStatus()` enforces that you cannot update a `WITHDRAWN` submission — once withdrawn, it is final.

