## 🛡 Duplicate Submission Prevention

`hasAlreadySubmitted()` scans the registry to ensure a Developer cannot submit twice to the same challenge:

```java
private boolean hasAlreadySubmitted(String developerId, String challengeId) {
    for (Submission s : allSubmissions) {
        if (s.getDeveloperId().equals(developerId)
                && s.getChallengeId().equals(challengeId)
                && !s.getStatus().equalsIgnoreCase(STATUS_WITHDRAWN)) {
            return true;
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```

Note: A withdrawn submission does **not** block re-submission. If a Developer withdraws their solution, they are allowed to submit a new one — this is intentional and fair.

